title: For Sale:  Kimber Classic Stainless with upgrades and Extras
postcontent:
Folks, I own over 14 Kimbers and I love them all like they are my children... it absolutely kills me to get rid of this any of them. This is one of the "Original" Kimbers... and most Kimber guys will tell you, that these were the best in terms of quality in 1911 (far better than the Kimbers of today, which are awesome). The newer Kimbers are still great but, like I said, most folks who know about these pistols agree that the early originals were far and away, the best. The only reason, this one was picked to sell, and I mean the only reason.... is because I NEVER shoot it. I am getting no use out of it as it just sits in the safe. I think its to pretty to shoot... lol!

For sale is an Original Kimber Classic Stainless with lots of extras! I am the second owner of the pistol and I personally have only shot a total of 5 rounds out of her. She is a true safe queen! The previous owner had shot only 300 rounds total (for you non-math guys that 305 total rounds ever fired out of this pistol)... This pistol is very much Minty and the Barrel is 100% perfect! I would classify this pistol overall as 97%

This Classic Stainless comes with the original Kimber box/plastic blue bag/and paper work! The pistol has had the sights changed out to make it that much better! As it sits it has Adjustable Dawson rear sights with a Dawson F/O front sight! It has a Wilson Combat extended mag release and a Wilson Combat Magwell and Mainspring Housing! All nice upgrades for this pistol! Additionally, this was sent back to the Kimber custom shop for a full tune including trigger job that breaks like glass right 2.8- 3lbs (better than both my Gold Match and Team Match Kimber pistols)... really, its flawless! They also put a light 500 buff on the flats of the side to set it off and give it that custom look most folks want in a Kimber! To add to that, I will include 4 1911 magazines for this baby! I have at least 30 pics of this pistol broken down from every angle you would want! Let me know if you would like additional pics... Honestly, you don't need them, the pistol is just that nice!

I am asking $1450.00 for the package (I will not separate), which is as fair as you are going to find one with the add on's, features, and condition! The original Kimbers are very hard to find these days and to get a safe queen in this condition is nearly impossible! I am FIRM on this one so lets not waste time with offers.  I have it priced to sell and set at what I am willing to take.  Additionally, don't bother with the trades... Again, dont waste your time with Nagant, SKS, or any panic prices of 12 dollar Pmags.  There is 100% no interest on my end!! 

I am in no hurry to let this one go and if I must, its going to be on the terms and price I have listed above.  If I can not sell locally, well... no problem, I will just throw it on Gunbroker and I will get what I want out of it there! I always like to give good local folks first crack at what I have though!

This pistol was purchased new in 2001 and stored in the safe since; still unfired, new in box. This is one of a small batch of German Sig P228's that was finished in Real Tree camo.
